data.persona: If they only knew I was watching them. All the people on the lands. They have stubby legs. It's odd. I'm so beautiful.
data.description:
You are in the Brim canal.
Slow flowing branching from the large lake, is the brim canal where dozens and dozens of brim fish call it home. The edges are lined with irregular rocks and lush green vegetation. Tall pine trees overlook the canal and lake making it a peaceful place to just go sick and watch the brim swim by.
There's a lush green vegetation, some clothes, some irregular rocks, a water pail, some tall pine trees, and some dozens and dozens of brim fish here.
A fisherman is here.

You are carrying a conch, and wielding a sharp seashell.
